        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 10:16AM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 1016 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mountain Home Air Force Base, or 11 miles west of Mountain Home,
moving north at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Mountain Home Air Force Base around 1020 AM MDT.
Danskin Peak around 1040 AM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
